<header class="introduction">

	<div class="container">

		<h2>Controls</h2>

		<p>
			Watercolor provides controls and classes that allow your web application to have a consistent feel for your users. Many controls can have additional class modifiers added to change behavior, such as: <code>primary</code> for default actions, <code>positive</code> for non-destructive actions such as add or save, <code>warning</code> for actions that require user attention, and <code>negative</code> for destructive or error conditions.
		</p>

	</div>

</header>

<section id="controls" class="container">

	<section id="button">

		<h3>Button</h3>
		<p>Having consistent button elements throughout your app is important. Add class <code>button</code> to any link, or use any standard <code>button</code> or <code>input</code> button element without the need for any classes.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<a href="#button" class="button">Link Button</a>
			<input type="button" value="Input Button" />
			<button>Button</button>
			<a href="#button" class="button" disabled>Disabled Link</a>
			<input type="button" value="Disabled Input" disabled />
			<button disabled>Disabled Button</button>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;a class="button"&gt;Link Button&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;input type="button" value="Input Button" /&gt;
&lt;button&gt;Button&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;a class="button" disabled&gt;Link Button&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;input type="button" value="Input Button" disabled /&gt;
&lt;button disabled&gt;Button&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

		<h4>Button Styles</h4>
		<p>A button style can be assigned to the button to provide visual clues to the user on the purpose of a button. Add class <code>primary</code>, <code>positive</code>, <code>warning</code>, or <code>negative</code> to any button.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>example</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button primary" href="#button">Primary</a></td>
					<td>Primary button style, use for the default form button. Add class <code>primary</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button positive" href="#button">Positive</a></td>
					<td>Positive, or success, button style, use for positive actions such as saving data. Add class <code>positive</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button warning" href="#button">Warning</a></td>
					<td>Warning button style, use for actions that require caution from the user. Add class <code>warning</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button negative" href="#button">Negative</a></td>
					<td>Negative button style, use for actions that delete data. Add class <code>negative</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

		<h4>Button Sizes</h4>
		<p>Size classes can be added to the button to make it more prominent, or to indicate it is an alternate action such as a cancel button. Add class <code>hero</code>, <code>large</code>, <code>small</code>, or <code>link</code> to any button.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>example</th>
					<th width="80%">description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button hero" href="#button">Hero</a></td>
					<td>Button sized for hero sections. Add class <code>hero</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button large" href="#button">Large</a></td>
					<td>Large button to give more emphasis over the default button. Add class <code>large</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button" href="#button">Default</a></td>
					<td>Default button size.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button small" href="#button">Small</a></td>
					<td>Smaller button to give lower emphasis over the default button. Add class <code>small</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a class="button link" href="#button">Link</a></td>
					<td>Link style button, commonly used for alternate functions such as cancel. Add class <code>link</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

	</section>

	<section id="tag">

		<h3>Tag</h3>
		<p>Use tags to display additional information such as item counts or categories. Add class <code>tag</code> to any span. Add class <code>primary</code>, <code>positive</code>, <code>warning</code>, or <code>negative</code> to any tag to modify the emphasis.</p>

			<div class="example">

				<span class="tag">1 item</span>
				<span class="tag primary">2 new</span>
				<span class="tag positive">3 complete</span>
				<span class="tag warning">4 warnings</span>
				<span class="tag negative">5 errors</span>

			</div>

			<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;span class="tag"&gt;1 item&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag primary"&gt;2 new&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag positive"&gt;3 complete&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag warning"&gt;4 warnings&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="tag negative"&gt;5 errors&lt;/span&gt;</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="label">

		<h3>Label</h3>
		<p>Use labels to display requirements, or other important information. Add class <code>label</code> to any span. Add class <code>primary</code>, <code>positive</code>, <code>warning</code>, or <code>negative</code> to any label to modify the emphasis.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<span class="label">info</span>
			<span class="label primary">required</span>
			<span class="label positive">success</span>
			<span class="label warning">warning</span>
			<span class="label negative">error</span>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;span class="label"&gt;info&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label primary"&gt;required&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label positive"&gt;success&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label warning"&gt;warning&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="label negative"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="badge">

		<h3>Badge</h3>
		<p>Use badges for notification counts. Add class <code>fb-badge</code> to any container element with style <code>position: relative</code>.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<span class="badge-image">
				<span class="fb-badge">1</span>
				<img src="/Content/Images/appicon.png" />
			</span>

			<span class="badge-image">
				<span class="fb-badge bottom-right">2</span>
				<img src="/Content/Images/appicon.png" />
			</span>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;span style="position: relative"&gt;
   &lt;span class="fb-badge"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
   &lt;img src="appicon.png"/&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style="position: relative"&gt;
   &lt;span class="fb-badge bottom-right"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
   &lt;img src="appicon.png"/&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;</code></pre>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 150px;">example</th>
					<th>location</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td rowspan="9">
						<span style="position: relative; display: block; margin: 1em auto; width: 96px">
							<span class="fb-badge">1</span>
							<span class="fb-badge bottom-right">2</span>
							<span class="fb-badge bottom-left">3</span>
							<span class="fb-badge top-left">4</span>
							<img src="/Content/Images/appicon.png" style="width: 100%; display: block;"/>
						</span>
					</td>
					<td>1 - top right. Add class <code>top-right</code>. (default)</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>2 - bottom right. Add class <code>bottom-right</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>3 - bottom left. Add class <code>bottom-left</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>4 -top left. Add class <code>top-left</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

	</section>

	<section id="modal">

		<h3>Modal</h3>
		<p>A modal panel that is displayed to a user after clicking a triggering link. Add class <code>.fb-modal</code> to any element, and any link pointing to it's target id will trigger the modal. Add class <code>slide-right</code>, <code>slide-bottom</code>, <code>spin</code>, <code>super-scale</code>, or <code>full-screen</code> to the modal to define the effect used while showing/hiding.</p>

		<div class="example">

		   	<a class="button" href="#modal-default">Default</a>
			<a class="button" href="#modal-slide-right">Slide Right</a>
			<a class="button" href="#modal-slide-bottom">Slide Bottom</a>
			<a class="button" href="#modal-spin">Spin</a>
			<a class="button" href="#modal-super-scale">Super Scale</a>
			<a class="button" href="#modal-full-screen">Full Screen</a>

			<div id="modal-default" class="fb-modal" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>
			<div id="modal-slide-right" class="fb-modal slide-right" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>
			<div id="modal-slide-bottom" class="fb-modal slide-bottom" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>
			<div id="modal-spin" class="fb-modal spin" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>
			<div id="modal-super-scale" class="fb-modal super-scale" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>
			<div id="modal-full-screen" class="fb-modal full-screen" style="width: 20em; max-width: 50%; padding: 2em;">Modal</div>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-default"&gt;Default&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-slide-right"&gt;Slide Right&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-slide-bottom"&gt;Slide Bottom&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-spin"&gt;Spin&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-super-scale"&gt;Super Scale&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="button" href="#modal-full-screen"&gt;Full Screen&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;div id="modal-default" class="fb-modal"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="modal-slide-right" class="fb-modal slide-right"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="modal-slide-bottom" class="fb-modal slide-bottom"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="modal-spin" class="fb-modal spin"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="modal-super-scale" class="fb-modal super-scale"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="modal-full-screen" class="fb-modal full-screen"&gt;Modal&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="disclosure">

